This article is a transcript of speeches given by First Lady Jill Biden and President Joe Biden at a Fourth of July event at the White House. The First Lady thanked military families for their sacrifices and expressed gratitude for their service. President Biden spoke about the importance of democracy and unity in the United States, and highlighted milestones in military history. He also emphasized the resilience of the nation and the need to continue working together. The speeches concluded with well-wishes and appreciation for the troops.